CAPE TOWN - Parliament's communications portfolio committee will deliberate on the SABC board interviews on Tuesday.On Friday, the committee concluded three days of gruelling interviews of 36 candidates.There are 12 places available on the public broadcaster's board. Members of the current interim board were among those interviewed.READ: SABC board candidate punts Checkpoint as favourite showThe interim board has been praised for doing a good job in restoring the public broadcaster's credibility.The portfolio committee will discuss the adoption of a report recommending candidates for appointment to the board. Schedule of Parliamentary Committee meetings dated 4 September 2017 https://t.co/oqr3YoD73seNCA